Success Nwogu, Abuja A former Vice-President, Atiku Abubakar, on Saturday lamented that Garkida in  Adamawa State was attacked by Boko Haram insurgents. He lamented the attack and decried the increasing attacks by Boko Haram insurgents. In his verified personal Twitter handle,  the 2019 presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party also condoled with the affected families in Garkida. READ ALSO: Lagos trader sells fake Total engine oil in Oyo, Anambra He tweeted: “The attack by Boko Haram against lives and properties of innocent Nigerians is unbecoming. “My prayers are with the people of Garkida in my home state of Adamawa over the cowardly attack that happened over the weekend. “May God give the affected families fortitude to bear the loss.”